# Windows Explorer thumbnails

Windows Explorer stores thumbnails in the thumbcache.
Such thumbnails can exist even when the original file has been deleted.

Thumbcache files are located in `C:\Users\username\AppData\Local\Microsoft\Windows\Explorer\`.


## Extract thumbnails via vinetto on Linux

The tool `vinetto` (https://github.com/AtesComp/Vinetto) can be used to extract thumbnails from thumbcache files.

Process a thumbcache file, extract thumbnails to an output folder and create an HTML report:
    vinetto thumbcache_256.db -o output/ -H

Instead of individual thumbcache files, it can also process directory structures.
